I"û<p>I think one of my favorite parts about sourdough is the scoring step. Its where you can make your loaf unique and bring out the artist in you. I have had some beautifully scored loaves and some really horrible ones. Here are some of the tips and tricks I have learned along the way.
You may be surprised to know that scoring has a huge impact on how your dough expands.
When your bread rises in the oven, scoring guides it to expand in a specific place. Expansion and tears occur in the weak points.</p>
